    "description": "Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners has an exciting opening for a Senior Doctor at our Dhanbad office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners:\nVijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Learning & development budget\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Dhanbad, Jharkhand, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners!",
